# Vue 3 & Frontend Standards for AuraStack

You MUST follow these frontend coding standards and design systems when editing or creating Vue components.

## 1. Composition API & TypeScript
* Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`.
* Type all props and emits using TypeScript compile-time macros:
  ```ts
  defineProps<{
    title: string;
    description?: string;
  }>()
  ```
* Bypasses the need for global state management like Pinia unless explicitly requested. Rely on page props for state where possible.

---

## 2. Design System & CSS Variables (app.css)
To maintain the premium look of the template, you MUST use the CSS variables defined in [app.css](file:///a:/auraflow/frontend/src/app.css). Never use raw CSS colors or ad-hoc custom Tailwind colors.

### CSS variables available:
* Primary Action: `var(--color-primary)` (default hover is `var(--color-primary-hover)`)
* Glow/Shadows: `var(--color-primary-glow)`
* Surfaces: `var(--color-surface)` (muted background is `var(--color-surface-muted)`)
* Borders: `var(--color-border)`
* Text colors: `var(--color-text)` (muted text is `var(--color-text-muted)`)
* Indicators: `var(--color-danger)` and `var(--color-success)`

### Custom Classes:
* **Glass Panel:** `.glass-panel` (applies backdrop-filter blur, border, and light/dark theme transparency). Use for containers, cards, and modals.
* **Inputs:** `.premium-input` (applies smooth cubic-bezier outline transitions on focus).
* **Buttons:** `.btn-premium` (adds overlay gradient highlight and hover animations).

---

## 3. Localization (i18n) & Bidirectional Layouts (RTL)
* **Translating Texts:** Always wrap user-facing texts inside the translation helper `t` from the custom composable `useI18n()`:
  ```ts
  import { useI18n } from "@/composables/useI18n";
  const { t, locale } = useI18n();
  ```
* **Dynamic Direction:** Layout directions are dynamically computed based on `locale.value`:
  `document.documentElement.dir = locale.value === "ar" ? "rtl" : "ltr";`
* **Tailwind Logical Properties:** To avoid UI layout breaks when changing languages, NEVER use physical position margins, paddings, or text alignment. Use logical alternatives:
  * Replace `ml-*` / `mr-*` with `ms-*` (margin-start) and `me-*` (margin-end).
  * Replace `pl-*` / `pr-*` with `ps-*` (padding-start) and `pe-*` (padding-end).
  * Replace `left-*` / `right-*` with `inset-inline-start-*` and `inset-inline-end-*`.
  * Replace `text-left` / `text-right` with `text-start` and `text-end`.

---

## 4. Inertia.js Page Integration
* **Data Retrieval:** Access authenticated user details and active workspace state directly from the page props:
  ```ts
  import { usePage } from '@inertiajs/vue3'
  const page = usePage()
  const user = computed(() => page.props.auth?.user)
  const activeWorkspace = computed(() => page.props.auth?.active_workspace)
  ```
* **SEO Components:** Ensure `<AppHead>` is included at the top of every page component to inject correct page title and metadata:
  ```html
  <AppHead :title="t('profile.title')" :description="t('profile.description')" />
  ```
